name: sewer grid construction, rural | sewer grid, rural | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/25575/documentation

The activity represents the construction of a sewer system for wastewater. The sewer system is used to transport 1 m3 sewered wastewater to the treatment plant and transports on average 1.6E09 l per year. The lifetime of the sewer system is 100 years including a renovation after 70 years.

The activity starts with the building materials available in the construction site.

The process includes building materials, end-of-life of the building materials, water consumption, machinery use and fuel input.
category: F:Construction/42:Civil engineering/422:Construction of utility projects/4220:Construction of utility projects
tags: Sector: Infrastructure & Machinery; Waste Treatment & Recycling

processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Underground sewer system for transportation of wastewater with pipes
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: Specific to the technology mix and human settlement structure encountered in Switzerland around 1996.
